---
import type { CollectionEntry } from 'astro:content';
export interface Props { font: CollectionEntry<'fonts'>['data']; }
const { font } = Astro.props;
const fam = font.fontFamily;
---
<div class="iu" style={`--fam:${fam}`}>

  <!-- 01 — BOOK SPREAD: drop cap, running heads, old-style figures, fi/fl/ffi ligatures -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">01</span><span class="label">Book — a typeset novel spread</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-book">
      <div class="iu__poster book" data-book>
        <!-- verso -->
        <section class="book__page book__page--verso">
          <header class="book__run"><span class="book__folio">42</span><span class="book__title">middlemarch</span></header>
          <div class="book__col">
            <h3 class="book__chap"><span class="book__chnum">Chapter the Fifth</span>Findings &amp; Keepsakes</h3>
            <p class="book__lede"><span class="book__drop">M</span>iss Brooke had that kind of beauty which seems to be thrown into relief by poor dress. Her hand and wrist were so finely formed that she could wear sleeves not less bare of style than those in which the Blessed Virgin appeared to Italian painters.</p>
            <p>It was hardly a fortnight after — the office clock striking five on a fine afternoon in 1829 — that the affair was first whispered of in the village. The figures of that year, set as old-style, dip below the line the way a compositor of the period would have cut them.</p>
            <p>She was open, ardent, and not in the least self-admiring; indeed, it was pretty to see how her imagination adorned her sister Celia with attractions altogether superior to her own.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
        <!-- recto -->
        <section class="book__page book__page--recto">
          <header class="book__run"><span class="book__title">george eliot</span><span class="book__folio">43</span></header>
          <div class="book__col">
            <p>And how should Dorothea not marry? — a girl so handsome and with such prospects? Nothing could hinder it but her love of extremes, and her insistence on regulating life according to notions which might cause a wary man to hesitate before he made her an offer.</p>
            <p>The morning of the fifth brought a sufficiency of difficulty: a flourish of letters, a file of accounts, and the inflexible Sir James waiting in the flag-stoned hall, his affliction entirely in earnest.</p>
            <p class="book__close">Yet she went down to him with the air of one who had already, in the quiet of her own resolve, decided everything — and would say so in the fewest possible words.</p>
            <p class="book__orn" aria-hidden="true">❦</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A real book opening — drop cap, running heads, 1829 in old-style figures, and live fi / fl / ffi / ffl ligatures in the recto.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 02 — ETYMOLOGICAL DICTIONARY: a single luminous entry; margin headword is the hero -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">02</span><span class="label">Reference — an etymological dictionary entry</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-lex">
      <div class="iu__poster lex" data-lex>
        <header class="lex__run">
          <span class="lex__guide">garamond</span>
          <span class="lex__pub"><span class="sc">A Dictionary of the Printed Letter</span></span>
          <span class="lex__guide lex__guide--r">gloss</span>
        </header>
        <div class="lex__body">
          <!-- outer-margin hero: the headword, oversized, with the live entry beside it -->
          <div class="lex__margin" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="lex__big">g</span>
            <span class="lex__fol">vol. <span class="lex__fig">II</span> · p. <span class="lex__fig">486</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="lex__entry">
            <h3 class="lex__head"><span class="lex__word">Garamond</span><span class="lex__pron">| ˈɡarəˌmänd |</span></h3>
            <p class="lex__gram"><em>n.</em> &amp; <em>adj.</em> &nbsp;<span class="sc">Typography</span>. &nbsp;Also <span class="lex__var">Garamont</span>, <span class="lex__var">Garemond</span>. <span class="lex__etym">[a. the punchcutter <em>Claude Garamont</em>, Paris, <span class="lex__fig">c.1510–1561</span>; the spelling with <em>-d</em> a later French regularisation.]</span></p>

            <ol class="lex__senses">
              <li class="lex__sense" data-sense>
                <span class="lex__num">1.</span>
                <div class="lex__def">
                  A roman type of the old-style, derived from the letters Garamont cut in the mid-sixteenth century; characterised by a slanted stress, small x-height, and bracketed serifs.
                  <span class="lex__cite" data-cite><span class="lex__year">1592</span>&nbsp;<span class="sc">Egenolff-Berner</span> <em>Specimen</em>: the <span class="lex__roman">Canon Romain</span> of Garamont, shown beside the italics of Granjon.</span>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="lex__sense" data-sense>
                <span class="lex__num">2.</span>
                <div class="lex__def">
                  Loosely, any of the modern revivals worked from that evidence — among them the faithful free <span class="lex__roman">EB&nbsp;Garamond</span>, in which this very entry is set.
                  <span class="lex__cite" data-cite><span class="lex__year">2011</span>&nbsp;G.&nbsp;<span class="sc">Duffner</span> &amp; O.&nbsp;<span class="sc">Pardo</span>: a Garamond cut from the <span class="lex__year">1592</span> sheet and the surviving punches.</span>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>

            <p class="lex__phrase"><span class="lex__phrW">— the Garamond gauge</span>, <em>fig.</em> the baseline of legibility against which a page is judged: <span class="lex__quote">“read by candlelight, it asks nothing of the eye.”</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A scholarly lexicon entry — small caps for grammar and cited names, true Granjon italics for etymology and quotation, old-style figures throughout. Hover a sense to draw its dated citation in.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 03 — INTERACTIVE OPENTYPE PLAYGROUND / READER UI (real px, device scale) -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">03</span><span class="label">Reader UI — live OpenType playground (real scale, interactive)</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene">
      <div class="iu__device reader" data-reader>
        <div class="iu__chrome">
          <div class="iu__dots"><i></i><i></i><i></i></div>
          <span class="iu__addr">read.egenolff.press/garamont-the-book-letter</span>
        </div>
        <div class="reader__bar">
          <span class="reader__logo">Egenolff</span>
          <nav class="reader__feat" aria-label="OpenType features">
            <button class="is-on" data-feat="liga" aria-pressed="true"><span class="reader__ftag">liga</span>Ligatures</button>
            <button data-feat="dlig" aria-pressed="false"><span class="reader__ftag">dlig</span>Disc.&nbsp;ligatures</button>
            <button class="is-on" data-feat="onum" aria-pressed="true"><span class="reader__ftag">onum</span>Old-style&nbsp;figures</button>
            <button data-feat="smcp" aria-pressed="false"><span class="reader__ftag">smcp</span>Small&nbsp;caps</button>
            <button data-feat="frac" aria-pressed="false"><span class="reader__ftag">frac</span>Fractions</button>
          </nav>
        </div>
        <article class="reader__body" data-text>
          <span class="reader__kicker">Essay · The Book Letter</span>
          <h4 class="reader__head">A letter cut to be read by candlelight</h4>
          <p class="reader__byline">Helena Vasari · <span class="reader__fig">12 June 2026</span> · <span class="reader__fig">9</span> min read</p>
          <p class="reader__lede"><span class="reader__drop">G</span>aramont sought no flourish for its own sake. He wanted a letter that would carry an argument cleanly across the page — and so the fi, fl and ffi ligatures close the gaps where a dotted i would otherwise crash into the hood of an f.</p>
          <p>Set the figures as old-style and the <span class="reader__fig">3</span>, <span class="reader__fig">4</span>, <span class="reader__fig">7</span> and <span class="reader__fig">9</span> drop their tails below the baseline, the way a compositor in <span class="reader__fig">1592</span> would have set the date on a title page. He priced a quire at <span class="reader__frac">1/2</span> a sou and a ream at <span class="reader__frac">3/4</span> a livre — flip on fractions and the figures knit into true cut ratios.</p>
          <p>Turn on the discretionary ligatures and the archaic <span class="dlig-demo">ct</span> and <span class="dlig-demo">st</span> bridges close — a deliberately old-fashioned touch reserved for a title page rather than running text. Set the cited names as small caps and <span class="smcp-demo">Egenolff-Berner</span> sits quietly inside the line without shouting.</p>
          <blockquote class="reader__quote">The most beautiful book types were cut not for beauty but for use.<cite class="reader__cite">— Beatrice Warde, after Garamont</cite></blockquote>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">Toggle each OpenType feature — ligatures, discretionary ligatures, old-style figures, small caps and swash italic all change live on the real column, and on the magnified “Live” chip.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 04 — LITERARY TITLE PAGE / INVITATION: swash italics, dlig, small caps -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">04</span><span class="label">Identity — a literary invitation &amp; title page</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-invite iu__scene--portrait">
      <div class="iu__poster invite" data-invite>
        <p class="inv__pre"><span class="sc">the bodleian library</span> &amp; <span class="sc">the egenolff press</span><br/>request the pleasure of your company at</p>
        <p class="inv__orn" aria-hidden="true">❧</p>
        <h3 class="inv__title">An Evening with<br/><em class="inv__swash">the Renaissance Letter</em></h3>
        <!-- swash flourish drawn in on scroll-into-view; final state = fully inked -->
        <svg class="inv__flourish" data-reveal viewBox="0 0 360 30" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
          <path class="inv__flpath" d="M16 17 C70 5, 120 5, 180 15 S290 25, 344 13" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          <path class="inv__flpath inv__flpath--tail" d="M180 15 C176 19, 170 23, 162 21 M180 15 C184 19, 190 23, 198 21" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          <circle class="inv__fldot" cx="180" cy="15" r="1.6" fill="var(--accent)"/>
        </svg>
        <p class="inv__sub"><span class="sc">a lecture &amp; private viewing of the</span><br/><em>Egenolff-Berner</em> <span class="sc">specimen of</span> <span class="jr-num">1592</span></p>
        <dl class="inv__details">
          <div><dt>Date</dt><dd>Friday, the <span class="inv__fig">12</span><sup>th</sup> of June</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Hour</dt><dd>Half past <span class="inv__fig">7</span> in the evening</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Place</dt><dd>The Divinity School, Oxford</dd></div>
        </dl>
        <div class="inv__foot">
          <p class="inv__rsvp"><span class="sc">r.s.v.p.</span> · by the <span class="inv__fig">1</span><sup>st</sup> of June · the press at <span class="inv__fig">11</span> Catte Street</p>
          <p class="inv__colophon"><span class="sc">printed in the letter of</span> <em>Claude Garamont</em> &amp; <em>Robert Granjon</em><br/><span class="inv__edition"><span class="sc">an edition of</span> <span class="inv__fig">240</span> <span class="sc">numbered copies</span> · № <span class="inv__fig">038</span></span></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A printed invitation — swash Granjon italic for the title with an SVG flourish that draws in on scroll, discretionary ct / st ligatures, small caps throughout, and old-style figures in the date and colophon.</p>
  </figure>
</div>

<script>
  // ---- 03 reader: live OpenType feature toggles on the real reading column ----
  // every toggle maps to a feature EB Garamond actually ships (liga/dlig/onum/smcp/frac).
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-reader]').forEach((reader) => {
    const text = reader.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-text]')!;
    const state: Record<string, boolean> = { liga: true, dlig: false, onum: true, smcp: false, frac: false };

    const apply = () => {
      const feats = `'liga' ${state.liga ? 1 : 0}, 'dlig' ${state.dlig ? 1 : 0}, ` +
        `'onum' ${state.onum ? 1 : 0}, 'lnum' ${state.onum ? 0 : 1}, ` +
        `'smcp' ${state.smcp ? 1 : 0}, 'frac' ${state.frac ? 1 : 0}`;
      text.style.fontFeatureSettings = feats;
    };

    reader.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-feat]').forEach((btn) => {
      const feat = btn.dataset.feat!;
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        state[feat] = !state[feat];
        btn.classList.toggle('is-on', state[feat]);
        btn.setAttribute('aria-pressed', String(state[feat]));
        apply();
      });
    });

    apply();
  });

  // ---- 04 invitation: SVG swash flourish draws in on scroll-into-view ----
  document.querySelectorAll<SVGSVGElement>('.inv__flourish').forEach((svg) => {
    const reduce = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
    // set each path's dash length to its own measured length so the wipe is exact
    svg.querySelectorAll<SVGPathElement>('.inv__flpath').forEach((p) => {
      p.style.setProperty('--len', String(Math.ceil(p.getTotalLength())));
    });
    if (reduce) {
      // arrive fully inked, no motion
      svg.removeAttribute('data-reveal');
      svg.classList.add('is-drawn');
      return;
    }
    const io = new IntersectionObserver((entries, obs) => {
      entries.forEach((e) => {
        if (!e.isIntersecting) return;
        svg.removeAttribute('data-reveal');
        svg.classList.add('is-drawn');
        obs.disconnect();
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.4 });
    io.observe(svg);
  });
</script>

<style>
  .iu__item { margin: 0; }
  .iu__hint { margin-top: var(--sp-2); color: var(--fg-3); }
  .iu__scene * { font-family: var(--fam); }

  /* shared: small caps + old-style figure helpers used across scenes */
  .sc { font-feature-settings: 'smcp' 1; letter-spacing: 0.02em; }
  .jr__fig, .reader__fig, .inv__fig, .jr-num { font-feature-settings: 'onum' 1; }

  /* ============================================================
     01 — BOOK SPREAD (container-query print sizing)
     ============================================================ */
  /* these print scenes grow with their content, so the poster flows in-place
     instead of being absolutely positioned inside a fixed-ratio mat */
  .scene-book > .iu__poster,
  .scene-journal > .iu__poster { position: relative; inset: auto; }
  .book {
    background: var(--bg); color: var(--fg);
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    /* every textual glyph in the book gets ligatures + old-style figures on */
    font-feature-settings: 'liga' 1, 'onum' 1, 'kern' 1;
  }
  .book__page { padding: 6cqi 5.5cqi 5cqi; position: relative; }
  .book__page--verso { border-right: 1px solid var(--line-soft); }
  .book__run {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline;
    font-size: 2cqi; letter-spacing: 0.18em; color: var(--fg-3);
    font-feature-settings: 'smcp' 1; padding-bottom: 4cqi;
  }
  .book__folio { font-feature-settings: 'onum' 1; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
  .book__col { font-size: 2.45cqi; line-height: 1.62; color: var(--fg); text-align: justify; hyphens: auto; }
  .book__col p { margin: 0 0 0.85em; text-indent: 1.4em; }
  .book__col p:first-of-type { text-indent: 0; }
  .book__chap { text-align: center; margin: 0 0 3.5cqi; font-weight: 400; }
  .book__chnum {
    display: block; font-size: 1.9cqi; letter-spacing: 0.22em; color: var(--accent);
    font-feature-settings: 'smcp' 1; margin-bottom: 1.6cqi;
  }
  .book__chap { font-size: 4.6cqi; line-height: 1.05; font-style: italic; color: var(--fg); }
  .book__lede { text-indent: 0 !important; }
  .book__drop {
    float: left; font-size: 11cqi; line-height: 0.72; padding: 0.5cqi 1.2cqi 0 0;
    color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500;
  }
  .book__close { }
  .book__orn { text-align: center; color: var(--accent); font-size: 4cqi; margin-top: 2cqi !important; text-indent: 0 !important; }

  /* a quiet living touch: the drop cap settles in on scroll-into-view */
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    .book__drop { animation: bk-settle 1.1s var(--ease, ease-out) both; }
    @keyframes bk-settle {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-0.06em); }
      to { opacity: 1; transform: none; }
    }
  }

  /* ============================================================
     02 — ETYMOLOGICAL DICTIONARY ENTRY (container-query print sizing)
     the oversized margin headword is the hero; the entry breathes beside it
     ============================================================ */
  .scene-lex { --card-ar: auto; }
  .scene-lex > .iu__poster { position: relative; inset: auto; }
  .lex {
    background: var(--bg); color: var(--fg);
    padding: 5cqi 6cqi 6cqi;
    font-feature-settings: 'liga' 1, 'onum' 1, 'kern' 1;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
  }
  .lex__run {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr; align-items: baseline;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); padding-bottom: 2.2cqi; margin-bottom: 5.5cqi;
    font-size: 2cqi;
  }
  .lex__guide { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); letter-spacing: 0.01em; }
  .lex__guide--r { text-align: right; }
  .lex__pub { text-align: center; letter-spacing: 0.16em; color: var(--fg-3); font-size: 1.85cqi; }
  .lex__pub .sc { font-feature-settings: 'smcp' 1; }

  .lex__body { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 30cqi 1fr; gap: 0 5cqi; align-items: start; }
  .lex__margin {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--line-soft); padding-right: 4cqi;
    position: relative;
  }
  .lex__big {
    font-size: 30cqi; line-height: 0.78; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-left: -0.04em;
  }
  .lex__fol {
    font-size: 1.85cqi; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--fg-3);
    font-feature-settings: 'smcp' 1; margin-top: 2.4cqi;
  }
  .lex__fig, .lex__year { font-feature-settings: 'onum' 1; }

  .lex__entry { font-size: 2.5cqi; line-height: 1.56; color: var(--fg); }
  .lex__head { margin: 0 0 1.4cqi; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.1; display: flex; align-items: baseline; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0 1.4cqi; }
  .lex__word { font-size: 5.4cqi; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .lex__pron { font-size: 2.4cqi; color: var(--fg-3); font-style: italic; letter-spacing: 0.01em; }
  .lex__gram { margin: 0 0 2.6cqi; color: var(--fg-2); }
  .lex__gram em { color: var(--fg); }
  .lex__gram .sc { font-feature-settings: 'smcp' 1; letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--accent); font-style: normal; }
  .lex__var { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg-2); }
  .lex__etym { display: inline; color: var(--fg-3); }
  .lex__etym em { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg-2); }

  .lex__senses { list-style: none; margin: 0 0 2.6cqi; padding: 0; }
  .lex__sense { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 4cqi 1fr; gap: 1.4cqi; margin-bottom: 2.2cqi; }
  .lex__num { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; font-feature-settings: 'lnum' 0, 'onum' 1; }
  .lex__def { color: var(--fg); }
  .lex__roman { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
  /* the citation is the hover-reveal payload: hairline-ruled, drops in beneath the sense */
  .lex__cite {
    display: block; margin-top: 1cqi; padding-top: 1cqi;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    font-size: 2.1cqi; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--fg-3);
  }
  .lex__cite .sc { font-feature-settings: 'smcp' 1; letter-spacing: 0.03em; color: var(--fg-2); }
  .lex__cite em { font-style: italic; }
  .lex__year { color: var(--accent); }

  .lex__phrase {
    margin: 0; padding-top: 2.6cqi; border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-size: 2.4cqi; color: var(--fg-2);
  }
  .lex__phrW { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg); }
  .lex__phrase em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
  .lex__quote { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg); }

  /* living touch: citations rest dim + collapsed, ink in when their sense is hovered
     (always fully visible under reduced-motion / no-hover) */
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) and (hover: hover) {
    .lex__cite {
      opacity: 0; max-height: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-top: 0; border-top-color: transparent;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: opacity 0.45s var(--ease), max-height 0.5s var(--ease),
                  margin-top 0.5s var(--ease), padding-top 0.5s var(--ease);
    }
    .lex__sense:hover .lex__cite,
    .lex__sense:focus-within .lex__cite {
      opacity: 1; max-height: 24cqi; margin-top: 1cqi; padding-top: 1cqi;
      border-top-color: var(--line-soft);
    }
    .lex__sense { cursor: default; transition: opacity 0.3s var(--ease); }
    [data-lex]:hover .lex__sense:not(:hover) { opacity: 0.55; }
  }

  /* ============================================================
     03 — READER UI / OPENTYPE PLAYGROUND (real px)
     ============================================================ */
  .reader { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; }
  .reader__bar {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.85rem 1.1rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 1.1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); flex-wrap: wrap;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--fg) 2%, var(--bg));
  }
  .reader__logo {
    font-size: 19px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--fg); letter-spacing: 0.005em;
    font-feature-settings: 'dlig' 1; flex: none;
  }
  .reader__feat { display: flex; gap: 0.35rem; margin-left: auto; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  /* buttons are set in EB Garamond itself — the UI demonstrates the face at true scale */
  .reader__feat button {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.42rem;
    font-family: var(--fam); font-size: 12.5px; line-height: 1; color: var(--fg-2);
    padding: 0.34rem 0.62rem 0.34rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 7px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line); cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.18s var(--ease);
    white-space: nowrap; background: var(--bg);
    font-feature-settings: 'liga' 1, 'onum' 1;
  }
  /* the leading tag is the literal feature code — quiet, lowercase, never shouting */
  .reader__ftag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--fg-3); padding: 0.12rem 0.3rem; border-radius: 4px;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--fg) 6%, transparent); line-height: 1;
  }
  .reader__feat button:hover { color: var(--fg); border-color: var(--fg-3); }
  .reader__feat button.is-on {
    color: var(--accent-contrast); background: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .reader__feat button.is-on .reader__ftag {
    color: var(--accent-contrast); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-contrast) 22%, transparent);
  }
  .reader__body { padding: clamp(1.6rem, 4cqi, 3rem) clamp(1.5rem, 5.5cqi, 4.5rem) clamp(1.8rem, 4cqi, 3rem); max-width: 64ch; margin: 0 auto; }
  .reader__kicker {
    font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; color: var(--accent);
    font-feature-settings: 'smcp' 1, 'onum' 1;
  }
